<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 8:34PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Rockdale, east central Henry and southwestern Newton Counties through
900 PM EDT...
At 834 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Rocky Plains, or near
Covington, moving west at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Conyers, Covington, Oxford, Porterdale, Magnet, Almon, Oak Hill and
Rocky Plains.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
